# Custom headers. Cloudflare Pages reads this file in the same format
# Netlify used (path line, then two-space-indented "Header: value"), so
# this rule carried over unchanged during the migration.
#
# CORS for the app version-check JSON: the My Namaz app's Capacitor
# WebView runs from https://localhost, so its fetch of this file is
# cross-origin and needs Access-Control-Allow-Origin or the response is
# blocked and the update check silently fails open.
#
# NOTE: on the *.pages.dev preview domain Cloudflare adds
# "Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *" to every response by default — it shows
# up on images and 404s too, so it is NOT coming from this file. Verified
# against the old Netlify host, which scoped it correctly to this one path.
# Re-check the custom domain after the DNS flip; if it is site-wide there
# too and that is unwanted, it needs a Cloudflare Transform Rule, not a
# change here.
/app-version.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
